OL,3,C'Undervalued' Guernsey civil servants
OL,4,Creject 5% pay offer
OL,6,F"The rejection of the pay offer is the
OL,7,Fonly tangible means by which members
OL,8,Fcan express their concerns about being
OL,9,Fundervalued and underappreciated;
OL,10,Fconcerns that have been growing year
OL,11,Fon year."
OL,13,FThe Association calls for Guernsey's
OL,14,FPolicy and Resources Committee to
OL,15,Ffollow through on its public support
OL,16,Fof civil servants by re-entering
OL,17,Fsalary negotiations.
OL,19,FNurses have already accepted the 5%
OL,20,Fpay offer while teachers' unions are
OL,21,Fstill in negotiations.
